gov.nasa.jpf.annotation

Annotation Type FilterField


  • @Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface FilterField
    Indicates that a field in the model should not be considered during state matching.
    Author:
    peterd

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String condition
      If not the empty string, specifies a property that must be "true" to activate this filter--unless invert is set.
      boolean invert
      If set to true, property must be "false" to activate filter.

    • Element Detail

      • condition

        public abstract String condition
        If not the empty string, specifies a property that must be "true" to activate this filter--unless invert is set.
        Default:
        ""

      • invert

        public abstract boolean invert
        If set to true, property must be "false" to activate filter. Does nothing if condition is empty string.
        Default:
        false
